Fix -Wincompatible-pointer-types error with GCC 14+ on 32-bit systems.

On 32-bit systems, int32_t is typically long int, which is a distinct type
from int. GCC 14+ treats -Wincompatible-pointer-types as a hard error by
default, causing the build to fail when &J (int32_t *) is passed to
mp_kronecker() which expects int *.

--- a/bn_mp_prime_strong_lucas_selfridge.c
+++ b/bn_mp_prime_strong_lucas_selfridge.c
@@ -95,7 +95,7 @@
       if (Ds < 0) {
          Dz.sign = MP_NEG;
       }
-      if ((err = mp_kronecker(&Dz, a, &J)) != MP_OKAY)            goto LBL_LS_ERR;
+      if ((err = mp_kronecker(&Dz, a, (int*)&J)) != MP_OKAY)            goto LBL_LS_ERR;
 
       if (J == -1) {
          break;
